steps.text:
This is already supported. `useThemeProps` is public from `@mui/material/styles` (and `@mui/system`) and can be used with a custom component key.

```tsx
import { styled, useThemeProps } from '@mui/material/styles';

const MyCustomComponentRoot = styled('div', {
  name: 'MyCustomComponent',
  slot: 'Root',
})(({ theme }) => ({
  padding: theme.spacing(1),
}));

function MyCustomComponent(inProps) {
  const props = useThemeProps({
    props: inProps,
    name: 'MyCustomComponent',
  });

  return <MyCustomComponentRoot {...props} />;
}
```

With the `name` on both `useThemeProps` and `styled`, the component can consume `defaultProps`, `styleOverrides`, and `variants` from `theme.components.MyCustomComponent`. The existing system styling documentation covers using `styled` with custom component names and theme variants.
